remost a preacher and pastor who guided souls and interpreted religious experiences. His primary tool in achieving these goals was the sermon, out of which grew many of his famous treatises. This selection of Edwards' sermons recognizes their crucial role in his life and art.The fifteen sermons, four of which have never been published before, reflect a life dedicated to experiencing and understanding spiritual truth. Chosen to represent a typical cycle of Edwards' preaching, the sermons address a wide range of occasions, situations, and states, corporate as well as personal. The book also contains an introduction that discusses Edwards' contribution to the sermon as a literary form, places his sermons within their social and cultural contexts, and considers his theological aims as a way of familiarizing the reader with the "order of salvation" as Edwards conceived of it. Together, the sermons and the editors' introduction offer a rounded picture of Edwards the preacher, the sermon writer, and the pastoral theologian.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCongregational churchesvSermons. 0aCongregational churchesxSermons. 0aSermons, Americanx18th century. 0aSermons, Americany18th century. 0aSermons, American. 7aRELIGION / Christian Ministry / Preaching.2bisacsh1 aKimnach, Wilson H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMinkema, Kenneth P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSweeney, Douglas A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300133639423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/978030013363